665":"1567–1665","1570–Female":"1570–Deceased","1574–Female":"1574–Deceased","1520–1594":"1520–1594","–Female":"Deceased","1 January 1565":"1 January 1565","1545":"1545","1567":"1567","1 July 1594":"1 July 1594","1665":"1665","about 1603":"about 1603","1520":"1520","1574":"1574","1594":"1594","1570":"1570","12 March, 1566":"12 March 1574","1603":"1603","Layston, Hertfordshire, England":"Layston, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom","England":"England","Norich,Norfolk,England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Ugley, Essex, England":"Ugley, Essex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bucke","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Buck  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Buck","meanings":["English: nickname from Middle English <i>buc(ke)</i> ‘male goat’ (Old English <i>bucca</i>) or a ‘male deer’ (Old English <i>bucc</i>). The goat was popularly associated with lecherous behaviour and the deer with timidity and speed. The surname may also be a shortened form of longer occupational names, for example Roger <i>le Bucmanger'</i> ‘dealer in bucks or venison’, (Warwickshire 1221) or Walter <i>Bucswayn</i> perhaps ‘goatherd’ (Somerset 1327).","English: topographic name for someone who lived near a prominent beech tree, such as <i>Peter atte Buk</i> (Suffolk 1327), from Middle English <i>buk</i> ‘beech’ (from Old English <i>bōc</i>).","German and Dutch (Limburg): from a personal name, a short form of <i>Burkhard</i> (see   Burkhart  )."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Bucke was born in 1545, in England, United Kingdom as the son of Thomas Bucke and Mary. He married Anne Calvert on 1 January 1565, in Layston, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters. He died about 1603, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1545–about 1603":"1545–umbes 1603","1545–1603":"1545–1603","1545–Female":"1545–Surnud","1567–1665":"1567–1665","1570–Female":"1570–Surnud","1574–Female":"1574–Surnud","1520–1594":"1520–1594","–Female":"Surnud","1 January 1565":"1. jaanuar 1565","1545":"1545","1567":"1567","1 July 1594":"1. juuli 1594","1665":"1665","about 1603":"umbes 1603","1520":"1520","1574":"1574","1594":"1594","1570":"1570","12 March, 1566":"12. märts 1574","1603":"1603","Layston, Hertfordshire, England":"Layston, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Norich,Norfolk,England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ugley, Essex, England":"Ugley, Essex, England"},"fi":{"1545–about 1603":"1545–noin 1603","1545–1603":"1545–1603","1545–Female":"1545–Kuollut","1567–1665":"1567–1665","1570–Female":"1570–Kuollut","1574–Female":"1574–Kuollut","1520–1594":"1520–1594","–Female":"Kuollut","1 January 1565":"1. tammikuuta 1565","1545":"1545","1567":"1567","1 July 1594":"1. heinäkuuta 1594","1665":"1665","about 1603":"noin 1603","1520":"1520","1574":"1574","1594":"1594","1570":"1570","12 March, 1566":"12. maaliskuuta 1574","1603":"1603","Layston, Hertfordshire, England":"Layston, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England","Norich,Norfolk,England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ugley, Essex, England":"Ugley, Essex, England"},"fr":{"1545–about 1603":"1545–environ 1603","1545–1603":"1545–1603","1545–Female":"1545–Décédée","1567–1665":"1567–1665","1570–Female":"1570–Décédée","1574–Female":"1574–Décédée","1520–1594":"1520–1594","–Female":"